The evidence with the title 'Is it time to tap Texas' rainy day fund? ' says Jan 14, 2011  ... Texas' $9.4 billion rainy day fund has never looked so plump, so ripe  ... And the state budget, facing a $27 billion shortfall, could use some stabilizing, say educators, employee groups and advocates for disabled Texans. Yet some lawmakers, and gov. Rick Perry, say now is not the right time to tap the fund. 
